cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper deals with pedestrian attribute recognition using deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel attribute aware pooling algorithm, which involves the use of context information and multi-branch architecture. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, since the paper deals with the recognition of pedestrian attributes, it may also belong to the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
